\title{Read Data Command}
\description{
An \link[R6:R6Class]{R6} class that wraps one or more character–taxon matrix
objects and renders them as a TNT \code{xread} command for use within a
\link{TreeAnalysis} workflow.

\code{ReadDataCommand} is created automatically when a matrix is supplied to
\link{TreeAnalysis} via its \verb{$data} field. Users do not typically need to
instantiate this class directly.
}
\details{
\subsection{Multiple matrices}{

Both \link{DiscreteMatrix} and \link{ContinuousMatrix} objects are supported, and
multiple matrices can be combined using \code{\link[=c.AbstractCharacterMatrix]{c.AbstractCharacterMatrix()}}
before being passed to this command. All matrices must share at least
one taxon in common.
}

\subsection{Command output}{

\verb{$render()} produces a multi-line \code{xread} block containing the matrix
dimensions, data type headers (e.g., \verb{&[proteins]}), and the
character–taxon data in TNT format.
}

\subsection{Queue integration}{

Calling \verb{$enqueue()} adds prerequisite commands before this command:
\itemize{
\item A \link{TaxonNameCommand} at priority \code{210}.
\item A \link{StateNumberCommand} at priority \code{200}.
}

This command itself is added at priority \code{220}.
}
}
